---
title: Tangy Plum Dijon–Glazed Chicken with Thyme Roasted Root Vegetables & Cauliflower Rice
description: Sweet, tangy, and all-around delicious—that’s the super-flavorful glaze you’ll drizzle over tonight’s juicy seared chicken cutlets. Sweet plum jam and zingy mustard balance each other out perfectly. On the side are simple, tasty thyme roasted root vegetables (carrots, potatoes, and red onion) to allow the chicken and sauce to take center stage. And boy, do they ever steal the show!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/652e9b89fa7d8680db86796d-c185c93c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6530109810949bb3e020f731.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 18 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 27 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 440 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tangy-plum-dijon-glazed-chicken-6530109810949bb3e020f731
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}.

Toss potatoes, carrots, onion, and garlic on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (For 4, divide between two baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks.) Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Spoon plum mustard glaze over chicken in pan.

> Swap in cauliflower rice for jasmine rice. Heat a drizzle of oil in a small pot over medium-high heat. Add cauliflower rice (no need to drain), and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and any excess liquid has absorbed, 6-8 minutes. Turn off heat; stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted. (Save jasmine rice for another use.)

In a #small bowl{}, combine @plum jam{1} and @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}. Set aside.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{} and pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about ½ inch thick. Season all over with @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat.

Spoon plum mustard glaze over chicken in pan.

Divide rice between #shallow bowls{}. Top with glazed chicken and roasted veggies in separate sections. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.